I"<p><span class="newthought">In order to be more effective</span>  at what I do<label for="1" class="margin-toggle sidenote-number"></label><input type="checkbox" id="1" class="margin-toggle" /><span class="sidenote">Principally, as a Senior Teaching Fellow at the University of Edinburgh, I help people become outstanding modern teachers of physics and science. </span>, I engage in personal and professional development work. I keep a record of this work in a development diary. Until recently, until the winter of 2019, this was over at my wiki<label for="2" class="margin-toggle sidenote-number"></label><input type="checkbox" id="2" class="margin-toggle" /><span class="sidenote"><a href="//cullaloe.net/w/">cullaloe.net/w/</a> </span>. This new channel is easier to post to, and in my view, is prettier to look at.</p>

<h2 id="tufte-and-this-site">Tufte and this site</h2>
<p>This site uses the <a href="https://github.com/clayh53/tufte-jekyll">Tufte Jekyll Theme</a> <label for="jekyll" class="margin-toggle"> ⊕</label><input type="checkbox" id="jekyll" class="margin-toggle" /><span class="marginnote"><a href="https://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a> is a lightweight system for creating and deploying websites using Markdown, Liquid, HTML and CSS. </span> by photographer and coder <a href="http://www.clayharmon.com/">Clay Harmon</a>, with a few modifications. It is hosted at <a href="https://cullaloe.github.io/CPD-Log/">GitHub</a> and at <a href="https://cullaloe.net/CPD-Log/">my VPS</a>.</p>

